source.data:
@Smoke

Feature: Run high level tests

This feature performs an End to End test starting form customer login to streaming

# Scenario: Check Registration page available
# Given I launch the Arcware application url
# When I click on 'Create Account' button
# Then I should be navigated to the Registration page

# Scenario: Verify new user can register 
# Given I land on the Registration page
# When I enter all the required details
# When I click on 'Register' button
# Then relevant successful message should be displayed

Scenario: Login user with correct email and password
Given I load the Arcware website
When I enter my userid and password
When I click on Login button
Then I should be logged into application


## //---- only for first time login - new tenant-----

#Scenario: Check for Get Started to proceed
#Given I am on Arcware Logged in page
#When I check for the 'Get Started' link
#Then I should be able to click the link

#Scenario: Check for all available plans
#Given I have clicked the 'Get Started' link
#When I am navigated to the Plan selection page
#Then I should be able to see all available plans 

#Scenario: Select Trial plan
#Given I can view available plans
#When I click to select Trial plan
#Then the Trial plan should be selected

##-----------------------------------------------------

Scenario: View Projects
Given I can see 'Projects' tab 
When I click to view the Projects
Then it should list all Projects

Scenario: Select Project
Given I can see all the Projects
When I click to select the desired project
Then I should be displayed with project details

Scenario: Navigate to Settings
Given I am able to view Settings option
When I click on the Settings Link
Then I should be able to navigate to Settings page

Scenario: Check General and Stream tabs
Given I am on Settings page
When I check General tab
Then I should see relevant General settings 
When I click on Stream tab
Then I should see Stream settings

Scenario: Check WebSdk tab
Given I have checked Stream tab
When I click on the WebSdk tab
Then I should be able to view WebSdk settings

Scenario: Check Project Plan
Given that Project plan option is available under projects
When I click on the Project plan
Then I should be able to view Plan details

Scenario: View Organization tab
Given I see the Organization tab on left
When I click the Organization tab
Then I should be taken to the relevant page

Scenario: View Organization page details General tab
Given I am on the Organization page
When I check for the General tab
Then I should be able to see all relevant details 

Scenario: View Organization page details other tabs
Given I am on the General tab page
When I check for the other tabs
Then I should be able to see all relevant tab details

#Scenario: Select package to upload
#Given I land on the Packages tab
#When I click on the 'Browse your package' option
#Then I should be able to add package for upload


# Scenario: Check Streaming for Preview
# Given I can see Preview option in the Project
# When I click on the Preview tab
# Then it should display streaming image

# Scenario: Perform release to cloud
# Given I click on the Package tab from the Project
# When I click on the release button
# Then I should be able to see the status
